                    <h2>Skills card for foreign workers postponed until March</h2>
                    <span>23/06/2024</span>
                    <p>The introduction of a skills card for foreigners seeking jobs in the tourism industry has been postponed from January until the end of March to enable it to be fine-tuned, Tourism Minister Clayton Bartolo has said.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        In October, the government announced that non-EU workers seeking employment in hotels, bars and restaurants must hold a skills card to work in the tourism industry in 2024, with plans to expand the skills card as a requirement for Maltese and EU workers in 2025.
                    </p>
                        <p>The scheme would bind third-country nationals applying for a work visa in Malta’s tourism industry to pass a skills assessment before their application can be processed.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://timesofmalta.com/article/skills-card-foreign-workers-postponed-march.1074888">Read more</a>
