                <h2>Non-EU workers increase tenfold in a decade to top 50,000</h2>
                <span>23/06/2024</span>
                <p>The number of non-EU workers in Malta increased tenfold in a decade, figures tabled in parliament on Monday show.
    
                    </p>
                    <p>In 2011, fewer than 5,000 foreigners from beyond the EU's frontiers were working in Malta. The number increased to over 50,000 people by August 2022.
                    </p>
                    <p>Answering a parliamentary question by PN MP Ivan Castillo, Employment Minister Clyde Caruana said 52,664 citizens from third countries were registered to work in Malta and Gozo on a full-time and part-time basis as of last August.
                    </p>
                    JobsPlus figures show that in 2011, 4,695 TCNs were working in Malta. That number gradually increased to 14,116 in 2017 and has continued to rise ever since, increasing even throughout the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>
